    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This type includes insects, arachnids, other arthropods, worms, and similar invertebrates.</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Features\">Features</span></h2>\n<p>Vermin have the following features.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>d8 Hit Die.</li>\n<li>Base attack bonus equal to 3/4 total Hit Dice (medium progression).</li>\n<li>Good&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Fortitude\">Fortitude</a>&nbsp;saves.</li>\n<li>Skill points equal to 2 + Int modifier (minimum 1) per Hit Die. Most vermin, however, are mindless and gain no skill points or feats. Vermin have no class skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span id=\"Traits\">Traits</span></h2>\n<p>Vermin possess the following traits (unless otherwise noted in a creatureâ€™s entry).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mindless: No&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Intelligence</a>&nbsp;score, and immunity to all mind-affecting effects (charms, compulsions, morale effects, patterns, and phantasms). A vermin-like creature with an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Intelligence</a>&nbsp;score is usually either an animal or a magical beast, depending on its other abilities.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/special-abilities#TOC-Darkvision\">Darkvision</a>&nbsp;60 feet.</li>\n<li>Proficient with its natural weapons only.</li>\n<li>Proficient with no armor.</li>\n<li>Vermin breathe, eat, and sleep.</li>\n</ul>",
